<item>
            <title>[CXF-7349] NPE in ClassLoaderUtils</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-7349</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A NullPointerException can be thrown when the JVM&apos;s boot classloader is set as the thread&apos;s context classloader.  Ex:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;URL url = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader().getResource(resourceName);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The call to getContextClassLoader() could return null - that is a valid return from that method.  In that case, we should use ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader() instead.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue was reported on in the users mailing list:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://cxf.547215.n5.nabble.com/NPE-in-cxf-core-ClassLoaderUtils-possible-bug-td5780007.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://cxf.547215.n5.nabble.com/NPE-in-cxf-core-ClassLoaderUtils-possible-bug-td5780007.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
